name: NDIS
summary: In response to concerns regarding recent modifications to the National Disability Insurance Scheme (NDIS), Bill Shorten has defended his handling of the support list. Shorten maintains that most participants will see no changes, while the new rules exclude ineffective treatments and introduce greater transparency. Critics, however, argue that the cuts will harm disabled individuals and undermine an already flawed system. The revisions forbid dubious practices such as crystal therapy, tarot readings, goat therapy, sex work, cuddle therapy, and vaping. The Federal Government has released a comprehensive list of approved supports, while Clean Group continues to offer home and commercial cleaning services to Paralympic athletes under the NDIS.

name: Tel Aviv
summary: Multiple news sources have reported a tragic shooting attack in Tel Aviv, Israel, resulting in numerous casualties. According to CBC and BBC, at least six people were killed and 12 injured in the Jaffa area of the city. National Post and Kathimerini English Edition reported seven fatalities in a shooting and knife attack, including a Greek national. Despite the attack, The Guardian noted that Tel Aviv residents remain unfazed by Hezbollah missile threats. Several international outlets, such as FRANCE 24, Global News Toronto, and Euronews, reported that multiple individuals were killed in the shooting attack. Additionally, Peoples Dispatch and Kathimerini English Edition mentioned missile attacks from Iran targeting Israel shortly after the Tel Aviv incident.

name: Alcaraz
summary: 19-year-old Carlos Alcaraz has become the second-fastest player to reach 200 tour-level wins, achieving this milestone in the China Open quarterfinals. In the tournament's final, Alcaraz faced off against top-ranked Jannik Sinner, ultimately defeating him in a thrilling tiebreaker to secure the China Open title. This marks the third time Alcaraz has triumphed over Sinner this year, highlighting their intense rivalry. Alcaraz's victory prompted an emotional exchange of messages between the two players, and Medvedev even shared a humorous joke with Alcaraz after their semifinal match. name: Julian Assange
summary: The Parliamentary Assembly of the Council of Europe has designated Julian Assange as a "political prisoner," emphasizing the detrimental impact of his severe treatment. In his first public statement since being freed, Assange asserted that he "pleaded guilty to journalism" to secure his release. Assange made his first public appearance after his release from prison and delivered a speech at a Council of Europe hearing. In his remarks, Assange stated that his decision to "plead guilty to journalism" was driven by a desire for freedom over elusive justice. Assange's remarks have generated discussion about his future, with observers speculating on his potential path forward.
